<subSubSection id="C34065156336FFC2FF12F974FC65F9B4" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="460" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6336FFCCFF12F974FB35F852" blockId="7.[151,1437,1666,1981]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6336FFCCFF12F974FE8AF972" bold="true" box="[151,269,1666,1692]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Remarks:</emphasis>
This specimen is labelled as 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6336FFCCFDCBF975FD26F973" box="[590,673,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">‘Typus’</emphasis>
both in the accompanying letter from Meyer and on the label (
<figureCitation id="13612A1B6336FFCCFAD4F974FF33F92E" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1359,1383]" captionTargetBox="[165,1429,190,1326]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[158,1430,181,1335]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 3. Labels of type specimens (maintained and refuted) in the NHMO Bird Collection described by A.B. Meyer. a) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (original Dresden label); b) Ptilopus flavovirescens NHMO-BI-59271 (NHMO label); c) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64131 (original Dresden label); d) Eclectus riedeli NHMO-BI-64132 (original Dresden label); e) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64130 (original Dresden label); f) Geoffroyus timorlaoënsis NHMO-BI-64228 (original Dresden label); g) Artamus Musschenbroeki NHMO-BI-68621 (original Dresden label)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6626769" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6626769/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Figure 3a</figureCitation>
), which seems to be in the same handwriting as the letter and therefore most likely written by Meyer. In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6336FFCCFEC9F93DFE60F90A" author="Meyer, A. B." box="[332,487,1738,1765]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="3 - 64" refId="ref15377" refString="Meyer, A. B. (1884) Ueber neue und ungenugend bekannte Vogel, Nester und Eier aus dem Ostindischen Archipel im Konigl. Zoologischen Museum zu Dresden. Sitzungsberichte und Abhandlungen der Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft Isis in Dresden, Abhandlungen 1884, 3 - 64." type="journal article" year="1884">Meyer (1884)</bibRefCitation>
stated that he based his description on a large series of specimens (
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6336FFCCFB64F93DFA0CF90B" box="[1249,1419,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">‘grossen Serie’</emphasis>
); 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6336FFCCFF12F918FE1FF8E6" author="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C." box="[151,408,1774,1800]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="233 - 316" refId="ref14237" refString="Eck, S. &amp; Quaisser, C. (2004) Verzeichnis der Typen der Vogelsammlung des Museums fur Tierkunde in den Staatlichen Naturhistorischen Sammlungen Dresden. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 54, 233 - 316." type="journal article" year="2004">Eck &amp; Quaisser (2004)</bibRefCitation>
specified the number of 
<typeStatus id="54E1883C6336FFCCFD29F919FC89F8E7" box="[684,782,1775,1801]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">syntypes</typeStatus>
in this series more precisely as 16, which also corresponds with the contiguous series of specimens recorded in the MTD catalogue (C7114–C7129; 
<tableCitation id="C6D803256336FFCCFB16F8E4FB6CF8C2" box="[1171,1259,1810,1836]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,239,656,680]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 2. Catalogue numbers from the MTD/SNSD catalogues of all 16 specimens in the type series of Ptilopus flavovirescens. Current locations and catalogue numbers are included for specimens for which this is known. Dresden catalogue numbers are not known for the three NHMW specimens or the NHMO specimen." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" tableUuid="DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E">Table 2</tableCitation>
). In addition to the 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176336FFCCFF46F8C0FEE5F8BE" box="[195,354,1846,1872]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
for which current location is accounted for in 
<tableCitation id="C6D803256336FFCCFCFBF8C0FC52F8BE" box="[894,981,1846,1872]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="8.[151,239,656,680]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 2. Catalogue numbers from the MTD/SNSD catalogues of all 16 specimens in the type series of Ptilopus flavovirescens. Current locations and catalogue numbers are included for specimens for which this is known. Dresden catalogue numbers are not known for the three NHMW specimens or the NHMO specimen." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" tableUuid="DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E">Table 2</tableCitation>
, there are also three in NHMW (NMW 
<geoCoordinate id="EE6E50596336FFCCFF12F8ACFF61F89A" box="[151,230,1882,1908]" degrees="48.234" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" precision="55" value="48.234">48.234</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE6E50596336FFCCFF63F8ACFEC4F89A" box="[230,323,1882,1908]" degrees="48.236" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" precision="55" value="-48.236">–48.236</geoCoordinate>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6336FFCCFECBF8ACFDD3F89A" author="Pelzeln, A. &amp; Lorenz, L." box="[334,596,1882,1909]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="37 - 62" refId="ref15941" refString="Pelzeln, A. v. &amp; Lorenz, L. v. (1888) Typen der ornithologischen Sammlung des k. k. naturhistorischen Hofmuseums. IV. Theil (Schluss). Annalen des K. K. Naturhistorischen Hofmuseums, 3 (1), 37 - 62." type="journal article" year="1888">Pelzeln &amp; Lorenz 1888</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6336FFCCFDDAF8ACFD7DF89A" author="Schifter, H." box="[607,762,1882,1908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="63 - 73" refId="ref16437" refString="Schifter, H. (1990) Dr. Adolf Bernhard Meyer und die Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Zoologische Abhandlungen, Dresden, 46 (3), 63 - 73." type="journal article" year="1990">Schifter 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6336FFCCFC80F8ACFC5AF89A" author="Schifter, H. &amp; Bauernfeind, E. &amp; Schifter, T." box="[773,989,1882,1908]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="1 - 376" refId="ref16471" refString="Schifter, H., Bauernfeind, E. &amp; Schifter, T. (2007) Die Typen der Vogelsammlung des Naturhistorischen Museums Wien. Teil I. Nonpasseres. Kataloge der wissenschaftlichen Sammlungen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 20 (Aves, Heft 1), 1 - 376." type="journal article" year="2007">
Schifter 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6336FFCCFCE1F8ADFC1BF89A" box="[868,924,1882,1908]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
; Hans-Martin Berg, pers. comm.), but it is not known which numbers from the Dresden collection these correspond to. These three, and the NHMO specimen, must however be assumed to be among the 
<specimenCount id="9D5CFD176336FFCCFD3BF854FCC4F853" box="[702,835,1954,1981]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">10 syntypes</specimenCount>
without known current location.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6339FFC3FF42FF4DFDD6FD8F" blockId="8.[151,1437,187,609]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
While no collection date was provided for the NHMO specimen, we have based the interval given for collection date (1881–1883) on information available in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6339FFC3FD23FF29FCC5FF17" author="Meyer, A. B." box="[678,834,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" pagination="759 - 774" refId="ref15281" refString="Meyer, A. B. (1881) Ueber Vogel von einigen der sudostlichen Inseln des malayischen Archipels, insbesondere uber diejenigen Sumba's. Verhandlungen der kaiserlich-koniglichen zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 31, 759 - 774." type="journal article" year="1881">Meyer (1881)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6339FFC3FCF8FF29FB9BFF17" author="Meyer, A. B." box="[893,1052,223,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" pagination="3 - 64" refId="ref15377" refString="Meyer, A. B. (1884) Ueber neue und ungenugend bekannte Vogel, Nester und Eier aus dem Ostindischen Archipel im Konigl. Zoologischen Museum zu Dresden. Sitzungsberichte und Abhandlungen der Naturwissenschaftlichen Gesellschaft Isis in Dresden, Abhandlungen 1884, 3 - 64." type="journal article" year="1884">Meyer (1884)</bibRefCitation>
. In the former, presented in 
<collectingRegion id="499EF87C6339FFC3FAE4FF29FA1AFF17" box="[1377,1437,223,249]" country="Austria" name="Wien" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Wien</collectingRegion>
on 
<date id="FFE4105E6339FFC3FF3EFEF5FE01FEF3" box="[187,390,259,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="1881-12-07">7 December 1881</date>
, Meyer listed specimens of birds received from Riedel, collected by him during a round trip of the eastern Malay Archipelago in 1880. The only species included from the Tanimbar Islands were 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FA8AFED1FE22FE8B" authority="Wallace, 1865" authorityName="Wallace" authorityYear="1865" class="Aves" family="Columbidae" genus="Carpophaga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Columbiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="concinna">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FA8AFED1FF79FE8A" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Carpophaga concinna</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6339FFC3FE80FEBDFE22FE8B" author="Wallace, A. R." box="[261,421,330,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" pagination="365 - 400" refId="ref16855" refString="Wallace, A. R. (1865) On the pigeons of the Malay Archipelago. The Ibis, 7 (4), 365 - 400. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1865. tb 06057. x" type="journal article" year="1865">Wallace, 1865</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(currently 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FDA6FEBDFC26FE8B" authority="(Wallace, 1865)" baseAuthorityName="Wallace" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[547,929,330,357]" class="Aves" family="Columbidae" genus="Ducula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Columbiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="concinna">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FDA6FEBDFD63FE8A" box="[547,740,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Ducula concinna</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6339FFC3FD76FEBDFC1EFE8B" author="Wallace, A. R." box="[755,921,330,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" pagination="365 - 400" refId="ref16855" refString="Wallace, A. R. (1865) On the pigeons of the Malay Archipelago. The Ibis, 7 (4), 365 - 400. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1865. tb 06057. x" type="journal article" year="1865">Wallace, 1865</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; from both Tenimber and Cera) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FAB8FEBDFF67FE67" authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1882" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Eclectus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="riedeli">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FAB8FEBDFF67FE67" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Eclectus riedeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(currently 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FEDBFE99FCB3FE67" authority="Meyer, AB, 1882" authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1882" box="[350,820,367,393]" class="Aves" family="Psittacidae" genus="Eclectus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psittaciformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="roratus" subSpecies="riedeli">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FEDBFE99FDE0FE67" box="[350,615,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Eclectus roratus riedeli</emphasis>
Meyer, AB, 1882
</taxonomicName>
; only from Cera). As no 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FBCBFE99FAD5FE67" authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[1102,1362,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FBCBFE99FAD5FE67" box="[1102,1362,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens were included in this shipment, it can probably be assumed that he did not collect this species during the 1880 trip. We have therefore concluded that the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FDF7FE41FCF2FE3F" authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[626,885,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FDF7FE41FCF2FE3F" box="[626,885,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens most likely have been collected at the earliest in 1881, and, as the paper in which the taxon was described is dated 
<date id="FFE4105E6339FFC3FC7DFE2DFB03FE1B" box="[1016,1156,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" value="1884-03">March 1884</date>
, they were probably collected no later than 1883. This also corresponds well with information provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB4B6F6339FFC3FBC4FE09FA8FFDF4" author="Buttikofer, J." box="[1089,1288,511,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" pagination="58 - 68" refId="ref13765" refString="Buttikofer, J. (1886) On a collection of birds from the Tenimber Islands. Notes from the Leyden Museum, 8, 58 - 68." type="journal article" year="1886">Büttikofer (1886)</bibRefCitation>
, describing a collection of 35 bird skins, including 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FDB3FDD5FCBEFDD3" authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" box="[566,825,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FDB3FDD5FCBEFDD3" box="[566,825,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, presented to the Leyden Museum by Riedel, collected by his hunters on 
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FEDBFDB1FE61FD8F" box="[350,486,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">‘Timor-Laut</emphasis>
’ in 1882.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E" ID-Table-UUID="DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2566166339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" startId="8.[151,239,656,680]" targetBox="[166,1410,769,1670]" targetIsTable="true" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8BE5369E6339FFC3FF12FD66FBC7FD1E" blockId="8.[151,1436,656,753]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FF12FD66FE8DFD46" bold="true" box="[151,266,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">TABLE 2.</emphasis>
Catalogue numbers from the MTD/SNSD catalogues of all 16 specimens in the type series of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D1D6339FFC3FB7BFD66FF7EFD22" authorityName="Meyer, AB" authorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ptilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavovirescens">
<emphasis id="B92EEA8C6339FFC3FB7BFD66FF7EFD22" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="459">Ptilopus flavovirescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Current locations and catalogue numbers are included for specimens for which this is known. Dresden catalogue numbers are not known for the three NHMW specimens or the NHMO specimen.
</paragraph>
</caption>
